A report in Fortune magazine said Airbnb is buying Trooly, a startup that specialises in technology that helps conduct background checks. Sarma, the companys Chief Technology Officer, is a gold medalist from IIT and has worked at Google Research and Yahoo Research. The Fortune report said an Airbnb spokesperson confirmed the acquisition but did not disclose the price or the number of workers involved. "We look forward to welcoming the Trooly team to Airbnb in the coming weeks," the Airbnb spokesperson said in the Fortune said. "Well continue working together to better facilitate trust between strangers on, off and across the platform ? 